 interest in mountain culture. She presents a compelling case for understanding wild spaces and human activity within them as parts of a whole. A work of invaluable scholarship in the areas of environmental history, public policy, sport studies, recreation, and tourism, Climber's Paradise will appeal to many non-specialists, mountaineers, environmentalists, and travellers across Canada and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAlpinismexHistoirex20e sièclexRocheuses canadiennes (C.-B. et Alb.). 0aLoisirs de plein airxHistoirex20e sièclexRocheuses canadiennes (C.-B. et Alb.). 0aMountaineeringxHistoryx20th centuryxRocky Mountains, Canadian (B.C. and Alta.). 0aMountaineeringzCanadian Rockies (B.C. and Alta.)xHistoryy20th century. 0aNational parks and reservesxHistoryx20th centuryxRocky Mountains, Canadian (B.C. and Alta.). 0aNational parks and reserveszCanadian Rockies (B.C. and Alta.)xHistoryy20th century. 0aOutdoor recreationxHistoryx20th centuryxRocky Mountains, Canadian (B.C. and Alta.). 0aOutdoor recreationzCanadian Rockies (B.C. and Alta.)xHistoryy20th century. 0aParcs nationauxxHistoirex20e sièclexRocheuses canadiennes (C.-B. et Alb.). 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh  aCanadian History.  aMountaineering.  aParks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212025740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772120257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772120257/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles